1.36.0 ¬∑ [source](about:blank/src/std/io/mod.rs.html#1387-1389)

Creates a new `IoSlice` wrapping a byte slice.

##### [¬ß](#panics)Panics

Panics on Windows if the slice is larger than 4GB.

[source](about:blank/src/std/io/mod.rs.html#1417-1419)

üî¨This is a nightly-only experimental API. (`io_slice_advance`¬†[#62726](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/62726))

Advance the internal cursor of the slice.

Also see [`IoSlice::advance_slices`](about:blank/struct.IoSlice.html#method.advance_slices "associated function std::io::IoSlice::advance_slices") to advance the cursors of multiple buffers.

##### [¬ß](#panics-1)Panics

Panics when trying to advance beyond the end of the slice.

##### [¬ß](#examples)Examples

```
#![feature(io_slice_advance)]

use std::io::IoSlice;
use std::ops::Deref;

let data = [1; 8];
let mut buf = IoSlice::new(&data);

// Mark 3 bytes as read.
buf.advance(3);
assert_eq!(buf.deref(), [1; 5].as_ref());
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0A%23!%5Bfeature(io_slice_advance)%5D%0A%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::io::IoSlice;%0A++++use+std::ops::Deref;%0A++++%0A++++let+data+=+%5B1;+8%5D;%0A++++let+mut+buf+=+IoSlice::new(%26data);%0A++++%0A++++//+Mark+3+bytes+as+read.%0A++++buf.advance(3);%0A++++assert_eq!(buf.deref(),+%5B1;+5%5D.as_ref());%0A%7D&version=nightly&edition=2021)

[source](about:blank/src/std/io/mod.rs.html#1457-1480)

üî¨This is a nightly-only experimental API. (`io_slice_advance`¬†[#62726](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/62726))

Advance a slice of slices.

Shrinks the slice to remove any `IoSlice`s that are fully advanced over. If the cursor ends up in the middle of an `IoSlice`, it is modified to start at that cursor.

For example, if we have a slice of two 8-byte `IoSlice`s, and we advance by 10 bytes, the result will only include the second `IoSlice`, advanced by 2 bytes.

##### [¬ß](#panics-2)Panics

Panics when trying to advance beyond the end of the slices.

##### [¬ß](#examples-1)Examples

```
#![feature(io_slice_advance)]

use std::io::IoSlice;
use std::ops::Deref;

let buf1 = [1; 8];
let buf2 = [2; 16];
let buf3 = [3; 8];
let mut bufs = &mut [
    IoSlice::new(&buf1),
    IoSlice::new(&buf2),
    IoSlice::new(&buf3),
][..];

// Mark 10 bytes as written.
IoSlice::advance_slices(&mut bufs, 10);
assert_eq!(bufs[0].deref(), [2; 14].as_ref());
assert_eq!(bufs[1].deref(), [3; 8].as_ref());
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0A%23!%5Bfeature(io_slice_advance)%5D%0A%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::io::IoSlice;%0A++++use+std::ops::Deref;%0A++++%0A++++let+buf1+=+%5B1;+8%5D;%0A++++let+buf2+=+%5B2;+16%5D;%0A++++let+buf3+=+%5B3;+8%5D;%0A++++let+mut+bufs+=+%26mut+%5B%0A++++++++IoSlice::new(%26buf1),%0A++++++++IoSlice::new(%26buf2),%0A++++++++IoSlice::new(%26buf3),%0A++++%5D%5B..%5D;%0A++++%0A++++//+Mark+10+bytes+as+written.%0A++++IoSlice::advance_slices(%26mut+bufs,+10);%0A++++assert_eq!(bufs%5B0%5D.deref(),+%5B2;+14%5D.as_ref());%0A++++assert_eq!(bufs%5B1%5D.deref(),+%5B3;+8%5D.as_ref());%0A%7D&version=nightly&edition=2021)

1.80.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/slice/mod.rs.html#4549)

Takes a `&[[T; N]]`, and flattens it to a `&[T]`.

##### [¬ß](#panics-3)Panics

This panics if the length of the resulting slice would overflow a `usize`.

This is only possible when flattening a slice of arrays of zero-sized types, and thus tends to be irrelevant in practice. If `size_of::<T>() > 0`, this will never panic.

##### [¬ß](#examples-2)Examples

```
assert_eq!([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]].as_flattened(), &[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]);

assert_eq!(
    [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]].as_flattened(),
    [[1, 2], [3, 4], [5, 6]].as_flattened(),
);

let slice_of_empty_arrays: &[[i32; 0]] = &[[], [], [], [], []];
assert!(slice_of_empty_arrays.as_flattened().is_empty());

let empty_slice_of_arrays: &[[u32; 10]] = &[];
assert!(empty_slice_of_arrays.as_flattened().is_empty());
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++assert_eq!(%5B%5B1,+2,+3%5D,+%5B4,+5,+6%5D%5D.as_flattened(),+%26%5B1,+2,+3,+4,+5,+6%5D);%0A++++%0A++++assert_eq!(%0A++++++++%5B%5B1,+2,+3%5D,+%5B4,+5,+6%5D%5D.as_flattened(),%0A++++++++%5B%5B1,+2%5D,+%5B3,+4%5D,+%5B5,+6%5D%5D.as_flattened(),%0A++++);%0A++++%0A++++let+slice_of_empty_arrays:+%26%5B%5Bi32;+0%5D%5D+=+%26%5B%5B%5D,+%5B%5D,+%5B%5D,+%5B%5D,+%5B%5D%5D;%0A++++assert!(slice_of_empty_arrays.as_flattened().is_empty());%0A++++%0A++++let+empty_slice_of_arrays:+%26%5B%5Bu32;+10%5D%5D+=+%26%5B%5D;%0A++++assert!(empty_slice_of_arrays.as_flattened().is_empty());%0A%7D&edition=2021)

