1.0.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/slice/mod.rs.html#1890)

Divides one slice into two at an index.

The first will contain all indices from `[0, mid)` (excluding the index `mid` itself) and the second will contain all indices from `[mid, len)` (excluding the index `len` itself).

##### [¬ß](#panics-13)Panics

Panics if `mid > len`. For a non-panicking alternative see [`split_at_checked`](about:blank/primitive.slice.html#method.split_at_checked "method slice::split_at_checked").

##### [¬ß](#examples-28)Examples

```
let v = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6];

{
   let (left, right) = v.split_at(0);
   assert_eq!(left, []);
   assert_eq!(right, [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]);
}

{
    let (left, right) = v.split_at(2);
    assert_eq!(left, [1, 2]);
    assert_eq!(right, [3, 4, 5, 6]);
}

{
    let (left, right) = v.split_at(6);
    assert_eq!(left, [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]);
    assert_eq!(right, []);
}
```

